  "title": "Senior Accountant",
  "description": "<p><strong>About the Role:</strong><br>\nOur clients are seeking a detail-oriented and experienced<strong> </strong>Senior Accountant to join their finance team. The ideal candidate will manage accounting operations, ensure compliance with financial regulations, and provide insightful reporting to support strategic business decisions.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Manage day-to-day accounting operations including accounts payable, accounts receivable, general ledger, and payroll.</li>\n  <li>Prepare monthly, quarterly, and annual financial statements in accordance with local accounting standards (e.g., SFRS, IFRS).</li>\n  <li>Conduct account reconciliations and ensure accuracy of financial data.</li>\n  <li>Assist in budgeting, forecasting, and variance analysis.</li>\n  <li>Ensure compliance with statutory requirements, tax filings, and internal controls.</li>\n  <li>Support audits by preparing schedules and documentation.</li>\n  <li>Collaborate with cross-functional teams to improve financial processes and reporting.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Bachelor’s degree in Accounting, Finance, or related field. CPA/ACCA qualification preferred.</li>\n  <li>Minimum 5 years of progressive accounting experience, ideally in [industry, e.g., manufacturing, services, or multinational environment].</li>\n  <li>Strong knowledge of accounting principles, tax regulations, and financial reporting standards.</li>\n  <li>Proficiency in accounting software (e.g., SAP, Oracle, QuickBooks) and MS Excel.</li>\n  <li>Detail-oriented, organized, and able to work independently.</li>\n  <li>Excellent communication skills and ability to interact with internal and external stakeholders.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Reg. No: R21103564</p>\n<p>EA License: 23S1921</p>",
